1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
This is JobsAgr — an autonomous job discovery agent
built on the ElizaOS framework.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Spinning up the local agent instance.
LLM runs on Nosana GPU cloud — no OpenAI dependency.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
This is the chat interface.
I'm giving it x.com/solana as the first target.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:18,000
The agent triggers its custom SCRAPE_X_PROFILE action —
profile → website → careers page → jobs.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Job board is empty right now.
Queuing x.com/arbitrum and x.com/layerzero_core.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Each target runs its own pipeline concurrently.
Watch the dashboard — listings are starting to appear.

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Actions completing in real-time.
LayerZero finished first — clicking a listing to verify.

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Live job posting page — pulled and stored
entirely by the agent. No manual searching.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Terminal confirms — Arbitrum's job links
fetched and being processed.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Dashboard — Solana, Arbitrum, LayerZero.
All three discovered and listed automatically.

11
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,500
Targets are entered manually for now —
but full autonomy is the next step.

12
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,000
A self-updating feed, any industry, any niche.
Powered by AI.